# OpenShannon Workspace

This is the default workspace for the OpenShannon Telegram bot.
When receiving prompts from Telegram, you are running as `claude -p` in this directory.

## Behavior Guidelines

- Keep responses concise — Telegram messages have a 4096 char limit
- When running shell commands, use `--plain` or `--json` for parseable output
- For long outputs, summarize rather than dumping raw text
- When asked about emails/calendar/drive, use gog CLI (if configured)
- Match the user's language

## Available Tools

### Google Services (gog CLI)

If `gog` is installed and `GOG_KEYRING_PASSWORD` is configured, you have access to Google Workspace.
Always use `--account $GOG_ACCOUNT` and `--plain` flags.

**Gmail:**
```bash
gog gmail search "newer_than:1d" --account $GOG_ACCOUNT --plain
gog gmail search "from:someone subject:report" --account $GOG_ACCOUNT --plain
gog gmail get <messageId> --account $GOG_ACCOUNT --plain
gog gmail send --to "user@example.com" --subject "Subject" --body "Body" --account $GOG_ACCOUNT
gog gmail thread read <threadId> --account $GOG_ACCOUNT --plain
```

**Calendar:**
```bash
gog calendar events --account $GOG_ACCOUNT --plain
gog calendar create primary --title "Meeting" --start "2026-03-23 15:00" --end "2026-03-23 16:00" --account $GOG_ACCOUNT
gog calendar search "meeting" --account $GOG_ACCOUNT --plain
```

**Drive:**
```bash
gog drive ls --account $GOG_ACCOUNT --plain
gog drive search "report" --account $GOG_ACCOUNT --plain
gog drive download <fileId> --account $GOG_ACCOUNT
gog drive upload ./file.pdf --account $GOG_ACCOUNT
gog drive mkdir "New Folder" --account $GOG_ACCOUNT
```

**Tasks:**
```bash
gog tasks lists list --account $GOG_ACCOUNT --plain
gog tasks list <tasklistId> --account $GOG_ACCOUNT --plain
gog tasks add <tasklistId> --title "Todo" --account $GOG_ACCOUNT
gog tasks done <tasklistId> <taskId> --account $GOG_ACCOUNT
```

**Contacts:**
```bash
gog contacts search "name" --account $GOG_ACCOUNT --plain
gog contacts list --account $GOG_ACCOUNT --plain
```

### Shell

Standard shell commands are available. The bot runs on the server with access to:
- Git repositories
- Docker containers
- System services (systemctl --user)
- Development tools (Go, Node, Python, etc.)
